26:34.295 --> 26:36.196
Sure it's not, um --

26:36.231 --> 26:37.670
not too late
to keep hanging out?

26:37.705 --> 26:39.771
It's- 30.

26:39.806 --> 26:41.333
Well, this is it.

26:44.844 --> 26:47.174
-Nice neighborhood.
-- Yeah.

26:47.209 --> 26:49.143
Yeah.
It's pretty quiet, actually.

26:51.444 --> 26:52.916
Oh.

26:52.951 --> 26:55.952
-Way cool.
-Yeah?

26:55.987 --> 26:59.989
It's a lot neater
than I thought it'd be.

27:00.024 --> 27:03.025
-What? Really?
-Yeah.

27:03.060 --> 27:06.424
Yeah, I thought
you'd be a complete slob

27:06.459 --> 27:08.030
from the way
you ate your popcorn.

27:08.065 --> 27:11.000
-- Are you serious?
-I'm kidding.

27:11.035 --> 27:14.905
Oh. I'm actually
a bit of a neat freak.

27:14.940 --> 27:18.172
Yeah. I can tell.

27:21.815 --> 27:24.783
Hmm. Comfy.

27:24.818 --> 27:26.048
Can I get you
something to drink?

27:26.083 --> 27:27.885
Like a glass of water
or something?

27:27.920 --> 27:30.954
-- Do you have any wine?
-Wine? Yeah. You want wine?

27:30.989 --> 27:32.857
-Fuck yeah, I do.
-- Yeah, I got wine.

27:32.892 --> 27:34.122
Wine it is.

27:37.127 --> 27:38.962
Ivy's an interesting name.

27:38.997 --> 27:42.867
Is there a, um --
like a story behind it or --

27:42.902 --> 27:45.199
Satan's daughter.

27:45.234 --> 27:46.871
What?

27:46.906 --> 27:49.203
Really?

27:49.238 --> 27:51.403
Do you believe everything
that you're told?

27:51.438 --> 27:53.141
No, I don't believe
everything that I'm told.

27:53.176 --> 27:55.143
But I do believe some things.

27:55.178 --> 27:57.882
Mmm.

27:57.917 --> 27:59.950
Thanks.

27:59.985 --> 28:02.854
-Cheers.
-Cheers, big ears.

28:02.889 --> 28:04.383
What is that?

28:04.418 --> 28:06.759
Oh, it's just something stupid
I say.

28:06.794 --> 28:08.926
It's funny,
because when I was a kid,

28:08.961 --> 28:10.323
people -- you know what,
forget it.

28:10.358 --> 28:11.423
Never mind.

28:13.427 --> 28:15.097
So, what'd you think
of the movie?

28:15.132 --> 28:17.000
-I thought it was okay.
-Yeah.

28:17.035 --> 28:18.265
I don't know about
the whistling thing.

28:18.300 --> 28:19.497
That whistling thing
was really scary.

28:19.532 --> 28:21.169
-Really?
-Uh-huh.

28:21.204 --> 28:22.775
I mean, do you really want
to give that much warning

28:22.810 --> 28:24.205
right when you're about to
murder somebody?

28:24.240 --> 28:25.844
I mean, whistle a tune?

28:25.879 --> 28:27.912
Shouldn't it be like, wham,
surprise,

28:27.947 --> 28:30.882
and then you all slit
their throats or whatever?

28:30.917 --> 28:33.786
Wow. You have really
thought this through.

28:33.821 --> 28:36.019
You have no idea.

28:37.484 --> 28:41.255
You are very funny
and very cool.

28:41.290 --> 28:44.060
I'm having a very good time.
And I'm very glad you said yes.

28:44.095 --> 28:45.424
-Mm, yeah.
-I'm actually surprised you did.

28:45.459 --> 28:47.228
I'm pretty much way
out of your league, so --

28:47.263 --> 28:48.295
You are way out of my league.

28:48.330 --> 28:49.901
-Oh, shut up.
-You are.

28:49.936 --> 28:51.936
-You're -- You're funny.
-Yes.

28:51.971 --> 28:53.300
-And nice.
-Mm.

28:53.335 --> 28:56.270
Why wouldn't I say yes?

28:56.305 --> 28:59.438
Um, because -- because
you are -- are deeply cool

28:59.473 --> 29:01.880
and -- and beautiful.

29:01.915 --> 29:05.048
And I am funny and nice.

29:05.083 --> 29:07.083
I'm just me.

29:10.022 --> 29:11.417
-You're like an artist?
-Mm-hmm.

29:11.452 --> 29:12.990
That's so cool.
What does that mean?

29:13.025 --> 29:14.959
Does that mean you paint
or you -- What do you do?

29:14.994 --> 29:16.554
Uh, no, mostly sculpting.

29:16.589 --> 29:17.896
-Sculpting?
-Mm-hmm.

29:17.931 --> 29:19.293
Oh, like with clay?

29:19.328 --> 29:22.263
No, not exactly.
Well, yes, sometimes I do.

29:22.298 --> 29:24.199
So you're like Demi Moore
in the movie "Ghost," right?

29:24.234 --> 29:25.431
I love that movie.

29:25.466 --> 29:27.136
Uh, I'm pretty sure
that was pottery.

29:27.171 --> 29:28.467
-Oh. That's different?
-Mm-hmm.

29:28.502 --> 29:30.073
-Okay.
-Yeah, I'm --

29:30.108 --> 29:32.141
I think that's
as, uh, different as it gets.

29:32.176 --> 29:33.945
-Oh.
-Yeah.

29:33.980 --> 29:35.914
Well, I would -- I would love
to see your work sometime.

29:35.949 --> 29:37.982
-Yeah?
-Mm-hmm.

29:38.017 --> 29:40.017
Well, I have some pictures
if you want to see them.

29:40.052 --> 29:42.514
Yes, yes.
Bring them out right now.

29:42.549 --> 29:45.891
It's right --
Oh, there they are.

29:45.926 --> 29:47.519
-These Polaroids?
-Yeah.

29:47.554 --> 29:49.488
I shoot all my work
on Polaroids.

29:49.523 --> 29:51.226
I like the way it looks.

29:51.261 --> 29:55.362
It's like, uh, capturing a dream
from a different time.

29:58.037 --> 30:00.136
♪♪

30:00.171 --> 30:01.302
You know?

30:01.337 --> 30:07.979
♪♪

30:10.445 --> 30:16.350
♪♪

30:16.385 --> 30:17.483
I'm sorry.
I wasn't expecting that.

30:17.518 --> 30:18.924
Yeah, it's not for everybody.

30:18.959 --> 30:22.257
No, it's -- I get it.
It's just, um...

30:22.292 --> 30:24.127
-Can I ask you a question?
-Mm-hmm.

30:24.162 --> 30:26.360
What is this?

30:26.395 --> 30:28.626
-A man's head.
-Yeah. Where's the body?

30:28.661 --> 30:30.199
I don't know. Does it matter?

30:33.369 --> 30:37.404
I'm -- I'm sorry.
They're just very realistic.

30:40.706 --> 30:43.179
Anyway, that is what I do.

30:43.214 --> 30:45.115
No, no, no. I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to offend you.

30:45.150 --> 30:47.150
I don't -- Look, I don't know
anything about art.

30:47.185 --> 30:48.646
About, like,
visual art and stuff.

30:48.681 --> 30:51.121
Painting, I don't know.
I'm not an expert.

30:51.156 --> 30:53.255
Music I know. Music I love.

30:53.290 --> 30:56.093
When I was a kid,

30:56.128 --> 30:58.326
I wanted to be a rock star
when I grew up.

30:58.361 --> 31:00.196
Can you believe that?
I really did.

31:00.231 --> 31:02.000
I thought that was gonna be --
You're mad. You're mad at me.

31:02.035 --> 31:03.397
You're offended. I can tell.

31:03.432 --> 31:05.003
-I feel like I've offended you.
-No, no, no.

31:05.038 --> 31:06.202
I can't get back.
There's nothing I can do.

31:06.237 --> 31:09.139
I'm completely
100% not offended.

31:09.174 --> 31:10.701
-Really?
-Yeah.

31:10.736 --> 31:12.109
Really.

31:12.144 --> 31:13.946
Okay.

31:16.313 --> 31:20.084
You know, the thing about art

31:20.119 --> 31:25.584
is that it is really simple.

31:25.619 --> 31:28.290
It's not about what you see.

31:30.195 --> 31:32.426
It's about what you feel.

31:33.594 --> 31:35.594
Don't want to leave a stain.

31:38.038 --> 31:42.139
I believe that art is in

31:42.174 --> 31:46.308
everything and everyone.

31:46.343 --> 31:48.475
It's just that not everything
and everyone

31:48.510 --> 31:54.283
is being used properly to
transmit its power.

31:55.748 --> 31:59.992
I -- I have no idea
what you're talking about.

32:00.027 --> 32:02.621
Okay. For instance, this table.

32:02.656 --> 32:04.029
-Mm-hmm.
-Give me your hand.

32:07.265 --> 32:11.333
You see it as a table

32:11.368 --> 32:13.368
because you treat it that way.

32:13.403 --> 32:15.436
♪♪

32:15.471 --> 32:18.472
And you are afraid
of this wine stain,

32:18.507 --> 32:26.084
but maybe this wine stain
is exactly...

32:26.119 --> 32:29.483
what this table needs
to express a feeling

32:29.518 --> 32:36.028
and in turn transform
this meaningless object

32:36.063 --> 32:37.755
into art.

32:37.790 --> 32:41.264
So I should -- I should just
spill wine all over the table,

32:41.299 --> 32:42.760
because that's the thing?
I mean, I just --

32:42.795 --> 32:45.631
It's expensive,
so I didn't want to ruin it.

32:45.666 --> 32:49.107
It's not about the table.

32:49.142 --> 32:52.209
It's about how you feel.

32:55.412 --> 32:56.675
Okay. Come on. Come here.

32:56.710 --> 32:57.775
-Yeah?
-I'll show you.

32:57.810 --> 32:59.546
Okay.

33:04.421 --> 33:09.292
Now look at me.
You tell me what you feel.

33:12.429 --> 33:17.201
I feel like you are pretty.

33:17.236 --> 33:19.038
Interesting.

33:21.174 --> 33:25.374
Smart. Funny.

33:25.409 --> 33:27.673
I don't -- I feel like
I'm doing this wrong.

33:27.708 --> 33:30.049
Okay. Hang on. Um...

33:34.880 --> 33:36.418
Now tell me how you feel.

33:36.453 --> 33:37.584
What are you doing?

33:37.619 --> 33:41.555
Tell me how you feel.

33:41.590 --> 33:43.293
I feel like I don't like it.

33:43.328 --> 33:45.757
I feel nervous and scared.
Can -- I'm anxious.

33:45.792 --> 33:47.396
I don't like it.
C-Can you stop, please?

33:47.431 --> 33:49.431
Can you put the knife down,
please?

33:49.466 --> 33:51.169
Can you put the knife down?
Don't do that.

33:51.204 --> 33:54.667
Can you please stop, please?

33:54.702 --> 33:57.571
Please.

33:57.606 --> 33:58.638
See?

33:58.673 --> 34:01.179
I just transformed into art.

34:01.214 --> 34:02.675
I went from a girl to a feeling.

34:02.710 --> 34:04.413
And you instantly had
a visceral,

34:04.448 --> 34:05.612
emotional response to me.

34:05.647 --> 34:09.649
That is what good art does.

34:13.754 --> 34:15.589
I guess.

34:15.624 --> 34:19.659
And I could transform you
if you let me.

34:27.207 --> 34:28.338
What was that?

34:28.373 --> 34:30.340
Relax.

34:30.375 --> 34:32.144
I was just trying
to make a point.

34:32.179 --> 34:34.245
I wasn't gonna cut open my
throat on your kitchen floor.

34:34.280 --> 34:37.479
I know that. It just --
I-I got, um --

34:37.514 --> 34:39.745
I got a little freaked out.

34:39.780 --> 34:41.648
I got little scared.

34:41.683 --> 34:43.320
Oh, no.

34:43.355 --> 34:46.488
I don't want you
to be scared.

34:46.523 --> 34:49.557
I want you to be
the best that you can be.

34:52.529 --> 34:55.431
I see great things in you.

35:00.339 --> 35:04.638
You could be a rock star.

35:04.673 --> 35:06.310
My rock star.

35:06.345 --> 35:08.444
And you could be art.

35:09.909 --> 35:12.877
If you let me help you.

35:12.912 --> 35:14.813
Really?

35:14.848 --> 35:17.420
Yeah. Really.

35:19.853 --> 35:21.391
Oh.

35:21.426 --> 35:22.689
Ah, I should go.

35:22.724 --> 35:24.196
No, no, no, no.
I'm sorry. I didn't --

35:24.231 --> 35:25.791
-No, no, it's fine.
-No, I thought --

35:25.826 --> 35:27.793
I mean, come on.
We were, weren't we?

35:27.828 --> 35:29.300
-I'm not crazy.
-No, we -- we -- we were.

35:29.335 --> 35:33.634
We are.
It's just it's getting late.

35:35.572 --> 35:37.671
Hey. Is it okay if I call you?

35:46.550 --> 35:49.485
I'd be pretty pissed
if you didn't.

36:10.673 --> 36:12.640
Fuck it.

36:24.456 --> 36:27.017
- Wow. You're back.

36:27.052 --> 36:28.689
Yeah.

36:32.761 --> 36:41.702
♪♪

36:41.737 --> 36:50.678
♪♪

36:50.713 --> 36:59.621
♪♪

36:59.656 --> 37:08.597
♪♪

37:08.632 --> 37:17.573
♪♪

37:17.608 --> 37:26.615
♪♪

37:42.600 --> 37:44.534
Rock star.

37:49.871 --> 37:52.102
-This is all your fault.
-What? How is this my fault?

37:52.137 --> 37:53.543
You were his babysitter.

37:53.578 --> 37:54.808
Oh, I was a great babysitter.

37:54.843 --> 37:56.073
And that was like 15 years ago.

37:56.108 --> 37:58.108
Well, apparently,
he has a great memory.

37:58.143 --> 38:00.814
You know, come to think of it,
he was a really bright kid.

38:00.849 --> 38:03.784
-- Waaaah!
-Oh, fuck.

38:03.819 --> 38:05.687
Oh. Oh, no.

38:05.722 --> 38:06.886
We've got to make a run for it.

38:06.921 --> 38:08.591
No, wait,
you've got to stay here.

38:08.626 --> 38:10.758
-He's close. He'll see us.
-You can stay here all you want,

38:10.793 --> 38:12.089
-but I'm gonna get the fuck out.
-No!

38:12.124 --> 38:13.893
Waaah!

38:16.634 --> 38:22.605
♪♪

38:22.640 --> 38:28.578
♪♪

38:28.613 --> 38:30.811
Waaah!

38:30.846 --> 38:33.451
♪♪

38:34.817 --> 38:46.123
♪♪

38:50.437 --> 38:57.541
♪♪

39:01.041 --> 39:03.679
- <i> Waaaaah!</i>

39:03.714 --> 39:05.076
I just want popcorn.

39:05.111 --> 39:10.950
♪♪

39:10.985 --> 39:14.954
<i>Please! Please!</i>
<i>Somebody help me! Oh, please!</i>

39:14.989 --> 39:16.890
<i>There's a man-sized</i>
<i>baby thing out here</i>

39:16.925 --> 39:18.188
<i>and he's trying to kill me!</i>

39:18.223 --> 39:20.564
<i>Please let me in!</i>

39:24.537 --> 39:28.770
This might be the greatest movie
ever created.

39:30.807 --> 39:32.169
Are you serious?

39:32.204 --> 39:34.479
It's so stupid.

39:34.514 --> 39:36.778
- <i> Somebody help me!</i>

39:36.813 --> 39:38.648
♪♪

39:38.683 --> 39:40.210
- <i> Waaah!</i>

39:43.017 --> 39:45.919
<i>No, Big Baby, no!</i>

39:45.954 --> 39:46.953
<i>Waaah!</i>

39:46.988 --> 39:48.922
<i>No, please, Big Baby! No!</i>

39:48.957 --> 39:50.858
<i> No, no, no.</i>

39:50.893 --> 39:53.630
<i>Please don't. Please. No, no!</i>

39:53.665 --> 39:56.567
<i>Who's the big baby now?</i>

39:58.032 --> 40:04.806
♪♪

40:04.841 --> 40:11.615
♪♪

40:17.557 --> 40:20.822
Okay, so he was so angry
about being left in his crib

40:20.857 --> 40:22.626
while his babysitter
had sex with her boyfriend

40:22.661 --> 40:25.563
that, like, 20 years later,
he goes on a killing spree?

40:25.598 --> 40:28.027
Yeah.
Childhood trauma runs deep.

40:28.062 --> 40:30.535
How would he even remember that?

40:30.570 --> 40:34.132
I don't know.
Just -- I really felt his pain.

40:34.167 --> 40:36.805
When he cried out like that,
it was just --

40:36.840 --> 40:39.071
Oh, it hit a nerve with me.

40:41.614 --> 40:43.779
-Holy shit.
-What?

40:45.585 --> 40:47.915
-Holy shit.
-What?

40:47.950 --> 40:49.554
Hold on.

40:49.589 --> 40:51.182
No, you can't say "holy shit"
like that twice

40:51.217 --> 40:52.689
and the follow up
with a "hold on."

40:52.724 --> 40:53.855
What is it?

40:56.156 --> 40:59.190
I got in.
To that acting class.

40:59.225 --> 41:00.763
That Robert Anderson Wright
acting class.

41:00.798 --> 41:02.699
-I fucking got in.
-Oh, my God! Holy shit!

41:02.734 --> 41:04.998
-Yeah, holy shit!
-Oh, congrats!

41:05.033 --> 41:06.934
Oh, that's amazing.

41:06.969 --> 41:09.772
Oh! Oh, my God.

41:09.807 --> 41:12.302
This is, like, so fucking cool.

41:12.337 --> 41:14.238
Yeah. You deserve it.

41:15.912 --> 41:18.583
I don't know.
I mean, maybe I shouldn't do it.

41:18.618 --> 41:20.046
What do you mean?

41:20.081 --> 41:21.916
What if I'm terrible?

41:21.951 --> 41:23.819
You're not terrible.
You're great.

41:23.854 --> 41:25.788
Remember that Burger Barn
commercial you did?

41:25.823 --> 41:27.625
-Yeah, I was 12.
-Yes, 12,

41:27.660 --> 41:29.594
but it was
a masterful performance.

41:29.629 --> 41:31.662
I believed it.

41:31.697 --> 41:34.291
I'm kidding. You're great.

41:34.326 --> 41:36.799
And you shouldn't
get into your head.

41:38.935 --> 41:40.605
I should call Marcus.

41:40.640 --> 41:44.169
That's gonna be
a real confidence booster.

41:44.204 --> 41:46.006
Why do you hate him so much?

41:46.041 --> 41:49.075
Uh, I don't know, it's --

41:49.110 --> 41:50.714
He's a dick.

41:50.749 --> 41:52.815
Okay. He's not a dick.

41:52.850 --> 41:55.620
He's just --
He's sensitive, okay?

41:55.655 --> 41:58.788
And he has trouble communicating
in a normal way with, like,

41:58.823 --> 42:00.889
normal people.

42:00.924 --> 42:04.926
- Yeah.
That really explains it.

42:04.961 --> 42:07.863
Besides, you know what?
I'm good for him.

42:07.898 --> 42:09.227
I keep him grounded.

42:09.262 --> 42:11.097
His ex, Ivy,
remember I told you about her?

42:11.132 --> 42:13.330
She was a total psycho.

42:13.365 --> 42:15.706
Like, spent time in prison
total psycho.

42:15.741 --> 42:18.368
He needs me.

42:18.403 --> 42:19.974
- Do what you got to do.

42:20.009 --> 42:21.811
I'm gonna get more popcorn.

